C.3 Round 1 Questionnaire

Instructions: Below is a proposed 9‑level Logistics Readiness Level (LRL) scale for planetary engineering. You are also provided with milestone lists for three historical megaprojects: Apollo program, Manhattan Project, and Panama Canal construction. For each milestone, please assign the most appropriate LRL level (1–9) based on the scale descriptions.

LRL Scale:

LRL Description
1 Concept formulation (peer‑reviewed paper, feasibility study)
2 Laboratory proof‑of‑concept for key components (TRL‑3 equivalent)
3 Component demonstration in relevant environment (Mars analog on Earth)
4 System demonstration in space (cislunar or Mars orbit)
5 Regional ISRU operational (one location on Mars, producing useful quantities)
6 Continental‑scale deployment (multiple sites, networked)
7 Global atmospheric effect detected (measurable change in climate)
8 PPE target achieved (300 mbar, liquid water stability)
9 Self‑sustaining stability (no Earth input required for maintenance)

Apollo Program Milestones:

· 1961: President Kennedy announces goal of landing a man on the Moon.
· 1962: First orbital flight of Saturn I.
· 1965: Gemini missions demonstrate rendezvous and EVA.
· 1967: Apollo 1 fire; redesign.
· 1968: Apollo 8 orbits the Moon.
· 1969: Apollo 11 lands on the Moon.
· 1972: Apollo 17 final mission.

[Similar lists for Manhattan Project and Panama Canal.]

Mapping Table:

